        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 1:22PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 122 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lynn, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Carbon Hill, Lynn, Double Springs, Nauvoo, Houston Recreational Area,
Camp McDowell, Ashbank, Corinth Rec Area, Poplar Springs, Lake
Buttahatchee, Winston Free State Barn, Smith Lake, Natural Bridge,
Weiss, Clear Creek, Winston County Airport, Cane Creek, Mill Creek,
Rockhouse Creek, and Delmar.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
